Colombian Stock Movers: Canacol, Pacific Rubiales, Ecopetrol

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-09-23T20:26:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/colombian-stock-movers-canacol-pacific-rubiales-ecopetrol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index declined 1.6 percent to 12,971.77, while the
Colcap Index lost 0.9 percent to 1,593.69.  Oil companies dropped as crude sank amid concern the global
economy is on the brink of another recession.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  South America , plunged 7.7
percent to 1,200 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in  Colombia , fell 3.7 percent
to 42,080 pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombiaâ€™s largest oil company,
fell 1 percent to 3,825 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
